This course covers the evolution of the business environment and the geographically defined economies in the Asia Pacific region. It covers all economies in the Asia Pacific Economic Cooperation (APEC) including China, Japan, Korea, south Asian countries, and the Association of Southeast Asian Nations (ASEAN). This course provides an insight into the geoeconomics and geopolitics in Asia Pacific and the strategies and organizational structures of companies from Asia, including the Japanese keiretsu, Korean Chaebol and Chinese state enterprises and family business.Objectives/eesmärkid:  Over the past two decades, the Asia-Pacific region has experienced a resurgence of economic activity and investment. More than the traditional flying geese model or Asian miracle as led by Japan, the rise of China in particular, is deemed by economists, sociologists and other academics alike as one of the pivotal development in the region. This course introduces students to the economic, political and sociocultural theories and frameworks for understanding the context of business in the Asia Pacific region and the application of contextual and local knowledge to the decision-making processes of companies operating in the region.Learning outcomes/õpiväljund:  By the end of this course, students will be able to: Learn more about socio-cultural, political and economic systems in the Asia Pacific region. 2. Identify business opportunities presented by emerging industries in the Asia Pacific region, and ASEAN 3. Gain insights into business and/or career opportunities in the Asia Pacific region and ASEAN.
